  "tcmTraditionalUsage": {
    "en": "Sweet in taste and neutral in character, hehuanhua affects the heart and liver meridians. It is used for calming the spirit, lifting feelings of sadness and treating conditions including insomnia and depression. It also invigorates the circulation and facilitates healing, making it a key herb for treating external trauma and injuries.\n",
    "zh-Hant": "合歡花性味甘平，歸屬心、肝經，長於安神解鬱，多用於虛煩不眠、抑鬱不歡、健忘多夢等症，常與首烏藤等安神藥同用。 《神農本草經》中記載：「主安五臟，和心志，令人歡樂無懮。」\n",
    "zh-Hans": "合歡花性味甘平，歸属心、肝经，长于安神解郁，多用于虚煩不眠、抑郁不歡、健忘多夢等症，常与首烏藤等安神药同用。 《神農本草经》中记载：「主安五脏，和心志，令人歡樂無懮。」\n"
  },
